post_cb({"16439735": {"ParentId": "16431216", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "2", "Body": "<p>This seems to be regression in gcc 4.8.0 because gcc 4.7.2 does compile both versions without errors. The Standard 14.1/2 specifically states that </p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_16431216_16439735_0\">There is no semantic difference between class and typename in a\n  template-parameter.</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "OwnerUserId": "819272", "LastEditorUserId": "819272", "LastEditDate": "2013-05-08T16:08:57.100", "Id": "16439735", "Score": "3", "CreationDate": "2013-05-08T11:40:59.857", "LastActivityDate": "2013-05-08T16:08:57.100"}, "16431216": {"CommentCount": "0", "AcceptedAnswerId": "16439735", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "819272", "CreationDate": "2013-05-08T01:28:38.573", "LastActivityDate": "2013-05-08T16:08:57.100", "LastEditDate": "2013-05-08T11:44:50.313", "ViewCount": "270", "FavoriteCount": "0", "Title": "Template alias not working in argument of template class template method", "Id": "16431216", "Score": "4", "Body": "<p>When I declare a template method of a template class whose argument type is specified by a template alias, I get a compile error. If I change the template class to a class, it compiles. If I replace the template alias by the actual type (here <code>Templ&lt;bool&gt;</code>), it compiles, too. Why doesn't it work, when it is a template class <em>and</em> the argument type is a template alias?</p>\n<p>The compiler is gcc version 4.8.0 (Ubuntu/Linaro 4.8.0-2ubuntu2~12.04).</p>\n<pre><code>template &lt;template &lt;typename T&gt; class Templ&gt;\nusing Bool = Templ&lt;bool&gt;;\n\ntemplate &lt;typename T&gt;\nclass Foo {\nprivate:\npublic:\n    template&lt;template&lt;typename U&gt; class Templ&gt;\n    void method(Bool&lt;Templ&gt; boolTempl);\n};\n\ntemplate &lt;typename T&gt;\ntemplate &lt;template &lt;typename U&gt; class Templ&gt;\nvoid Foo&lt;T&gt;::method(Bool&lt;Templ&gt; boolTempl) {\n}\n\nint main() {\n    Foo&lt;char&gt; foo;\n    return 0;\n}\n\ng++ templTest12.C -o templTest12 -std=c++11\ntemplTest12.C: In substitution of `template&lt;template&lt;class T&gt; class Templ&gt; using Bool = Templ&lt;bool&gt; [with Templ = Templ]':\ntemplTest12.C:17:6:   required from `class Foo&lt;char&gt;'\ntemplTest12.C:30:12:   required from here\ntemplTest12.C:2:25: error: `template&lt;class U&gt; class Templ' is not a template\n using Bool = Templ&lt;bool&gt;;\n</code></pre>\n", "Tags": "<c++><templates><gcc><c++11><template-aliases>", "OwnerUserId": "2360448", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_16431216_16439735_0": {"section_id": 55, "quality": 1.0, "length": 7}}, "n3337": {"so_16431216_16439735_0": {"section_id": 50, "quality": 1.0, "length": 7}}, "n4659": {"so_16431216_16439735_0": {"section_id": 57, "quality": 1.0, "length": 7}}}});